At Level 1, utilize Trusted Execution (TE) to log execution of applications not yet allowlisted. This can be used to update the allowlist (TSD -           
                      /etc/security/tsd/tsd.dat
) so that, at Profile Level 2, non-listed applications are actually prevented from executing.

